The Story of Sunlights starts with Jamison Shaw. 💛​​​​​​​​​JAMISON THOMAS SHAW | March 2, 1936 – July 17, 2023
In 1960, at age 24, Jamison opened his first salon in Atlanta.  A world champion competition hairdresser, Jamison’s closest friends included the likes of Vidal Sassoon, Paul Mitchell, and Horst, Aveda’s founder.  Jamison would say: “we all knew and competed against each other back when we were so broke not one of us had two dimes in his pocket to rub together!” In 1962, Shaw rose to prominence as the first American to win hairdressing’s Grand World Supreme Championships in Holland in the marcel iron competition.  Prior to that time, the century-old honor had only been won by the great European stylists.  Returning home as America’s first World Champion, Shaw appeared on the Ed Sullivan Show (where the Beatles and Elvis Presley both debuted) and in Time magazine.  Shaw remained at the forefront of the international hairdressing scene ever since and is widely regarded as one of the top hairstylists of the 20th century.

In lieu of flowers the family asks that you please consider making a donation to Beauty Changes Lives, a non-profit organization whose mission is to provide cosmetology school scholarships to aspiring beauty professionals to help ensure the future of the beauty industry he so loved.
